parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the piston rings can cause the engine to misfire, resulting in a loss of power, rough idling, and decreased fuel efficiency. This can lead to accidents, especially when driving on highways, and can also cause damage to other engine components.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
flashing or steady; the engine misfires
causing a loss of power; the vehicle shakes or vibrates; the odor of burning oil is present; the engine runs rough; and the vehicle may stall or hesitate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and juddering can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or judders when shifting gears
especially between 20-65 mph; the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating; the transmission makes a clunking or banging noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The torque converter failure can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shudders or vibrates when accelerating; the transmission slips or judders when shifting gears; the torque converter makes a loud noise or produces metal shavings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch master cylinder failure can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Variable Cylinder Management system failure can cause the engine to seize up, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine seizes up without warning; the vehicle loses power and cannot accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The keyless entry computer board failure can cause the vehicle to roll away or start without the key, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls away or starts without the key; the keyless entry system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning; the vehicle loses power and cannot accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The axle nut not being tightened can cause the axle to come loose, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A thunking noise is heard from the left front wheel; the axle nut is loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the loss of power, stalling, and sudden shutdown of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Dashboard warning lights
radio
and rear and side cameras shutting off and then turning back on
loss of power
stalling
and sudden shutdown of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the sliding door can cause entrapment, injury, or even death, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: Sliding doors not opening or closing properly
doors closing abruptly on their own
and doors not recognizing obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and hydraulic system can cause the loss of power, stalling, and sudden shutdown of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticking to the floor
and failure of the clutch master cylinder.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator and battery can cause the loss of power, stalling, and sudden shutdown of the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Alternator failure
battery drain
and failure of the electrical system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and safety system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbag failure
safety system malfunction
and failure of the backup camera.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the second row seat frame can cause the seat to tip forward or become loose, which can lead to accidents or injuries to passengers.
symptoms: The second row seat tips forward or becomes loose
the seat back frame collapses
the seat does not latch properly
the seat slides while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The head restraint design can cause discomfort, pain, and distraction while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The head restraint pushes the head forward
causes neck and back pain
makes it difficult to look straight ahead
forces the driver to slouch or recline the seat.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Blind Spot Caused by Third Row Head Restraints
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The third row head restraints can cause a large blind spot, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The third row head restraints cover a significant portion of the rear window
causing a blind spot.
